caption: Table 1: Random choice selection performance on English and Portuguese versions of 2022 test 4 subjects.
description: This table presents the results of a random choice selection experiment conducted on English and Portuguese versions of the 2022 test.  It shows the accuracy (CTT) scores, the ability levels (θ), and the l2 scores for four subjects (humanities, languages, science, math) in both languages.  The data helps to evaluate the consistency of model performance and compare it to human responses in different language contexts. The metrics used provide insights into model capabilities and reveal discrepancies between model and human responses.

caption: Table 1: Random choice selection performance on English and Portuguese versions of 2022 test 4 subjects.
description: This table presents the results of a random choice selection experiment conducted on English and Portuguese versions of a 2022 test for four subjects (Humanities, Languages, Science, and Math).  For each subject and language, it shows the average accuracy (CTT score), the average ability level (θ score from Item Response Theory model), and the average l₂ score, which measures the consistency of the test takers' response patterns with the model.  The table helps to assess the performance of the test subjects and highlight any discrepancies between the two languages.

caption: Table 1: Random choice selection performance on English and Portuguese versions of 2022 test 4 subjects.
description: This table shows the performance of a random choice selection on the English and Portuguese versions of the 2022 test for four subjects (Humanities, Languages, Natural Sciences, and Math).  For each subject and language, it presents the mean accuracy (CTT score), the mean ability level (θ), and the mean l₂ score (goodness-of-fit). The standard deviations are also included to show the variability in these measures.
